body:
`CMakePackage` class has `depends_on('cmake', type='build')` and the oldest cmake version we have is 2.8.10.2, so
```
$ git grep --files-with-matches CMakePackage var/spack/repos | xargs grep -E "depends_on.*cmake('|@2.8)" | grep -v 2.8.1[12]
var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/cppad/package.py:    depends_on('cmake', type='build')
var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/cuda-memtest/package.py:    depends_on('cmake@2.8.5:', type='build')
var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/elemental/package.py:    depends_on('cmake', type='build')
var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/espressopp/package.py:    depends_on("cmake@2.8:", type='build')
var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/gmsh/package.py:    depends_on('cmake@2.8:', type='build')
var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/gromacs/package.py:    depends_on('cmake@2.8.8:', type='build')
var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/libgit2/package.py:    depends_on('cmake@2.8:', type='build')
var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/libsplash/package.py:    depends_on('cmake', type='build')
var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/netlib-scalapack/package.py:    depends_on('cmake', when='@2.0.0:', type='build')
var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/pagmo/package.py:    depends_on('cmake@2.8:', type='build')
var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/pngwriter/package.py:    depends_on('cmake', type='build')
var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/shiny-server/package.py:    depends_on('cmake@2.8.10:')
var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/symengine/package.py:    depends_on('cmake',    type='build')
var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/votca-csg/package.py:    depends_on("cmake@2.8:", type='build')
var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/votca-tools/package.py:    depends_on("cmake@2.8:", type='build')
```
for these packages we could remove the `depends_on("cmake.*")` line.
